       button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\">\n            <h1>Big-O Notation</h1>\n            <p>Learn about the time complexity of algorithms and data structures</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"content\">\n            <h2>What is Big-O Notation?</h2>\n            <p>Big-O notation is a way to measure the time and space complexity of an algorithm or data structure.</p>\n            <h2>Time Complexity</h2>\n            <p>Time complexity is a measure of an algorithm's performance, usually expressed as a function of the input size.</p>\n            <h2>Space Complexity</h2>\n            <p>Space complexity is a measure of an algorithm's memory usage, usually expressed as a function of the input size.</p>\n            <button id=\"time-btn\">Time Complexity</button>\n            <button id=\"space-btn\">Space Complexity</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"footer\">\n            <p>&copy; 2023 Big-O Notation</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        const timeBtn = document.getElementById('time-btn');\n        const spaceBtn = document.getElementById('space-btn');\n\n        timeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            alert('Time complexity: O(n) or O(n^2)');\n        });\n\n        spaceBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            alert('Space complexity: O(1) or O(n)');\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
